The $m$ vs $r$ plot is shown in Fig.\ref{fig:fixedpoints} for $b=0.99$, and all the critical points are marked. One important characteristic of this model compared to many previously analysed model is that the  plot is multivalued. The upper and lower branch is separated by the line $m = -r -1$. As we move clockwise along the curve the scalar curvature $R$ decreases with point $P_5 (r\sim-1,m\simeq +0)$ corresponding to both small and high curvature limits. 

